import Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Preadditive.AdditiveFunctor
import Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Linear.Basic

/-!
# Example 7.9.2: Additive and k-linear Functors in Representation Theory

The functors Ind_K^G, Res_K^G, Hom_G(V, ?) in the theory of group representations
over a field k are additive and k-linear.

## Mathlib correspondence

These functors being additive/linear follows from their construction in Mathlib's
representation theory library.
-/

open CategoryTheory

/-- The restriction, induction, and Hom functors in group representation theory
are additive and k-linear. (Etingof Example 7.9.2) -/
theorem Etingof.rep_functors_additive_linear : (sorry : Prop) := by sorry
